docsQos3DSCRsps.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Change section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DSCRsps.description: The number of Dynamic Service Change Responses, including retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DSCAcks.name: docsQos3DSCAcks
docsQos3DSCAcks.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Change section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DSCAcks.description: The number of Dynamic Service Change Acknowledgements, including retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DSDReqs.name: docsQos3DSDReqs
docsQos3DSDReqs.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Delete section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DSDReqs.description: The number of Dynamic Service Delete Requests, including retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DSDRsps.name: docsQos3DSDRsps
docsQos3DSDRsps.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Delete section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DSDRsps.description: The number of Dynamic Service Delete Responses, including retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DynamicAdds.name: docsQos3DynamicAdds
docsQos3DynamicAdds.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Addition section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DynamicAdds.description: The number of successful Dynamic Service Addition transactions. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DynamicAddFails.name: docsQos3DynamicAddFails
docsQos3DynamicAddFails.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Addition section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DynamicAddFails.description: The number of failed Dynamic Service Addition transactions. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DynamicChanges.name: docsQos3DynamicChanges
docsQos3DynamicChanges.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Change section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DynamicChanges.description: The number of successful Dynamic Service Change transactions. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DynamicChangeFails.name: docsQos3DynamicChangeFails
docsQos3DynamicChangeFails.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Change section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DynamicChangeFails.description: The number of failed Dynamic Service Change transactions. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DynamicDeletes.name: docsQos3DynamicDeletes
docsQos3DynamicDeletes.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Delete section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DynamicDeletes.description: The number of successful Dynamic Service Delete transactions. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DynamicDeleteFails.name: docsQos3DynamicDeleteFails
docsQos3DynamicDeleteFails.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Service Delete section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DynamicDeleteFails.description: The number of failed Dynamic Service Delete transactions. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCReqs.name: docsQos3DCCReqs
docsQos3DCCReqs.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCReqs.description: The number of Dynamic Channel Change Request messages traversing an interface. This count is nonzero only on downstream direction rows. This count should include the number of retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCRsps.name: docsQos3DCCRsps
docsQos3DCCRsps.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCRsps.description: The number of Dynamic Channel Change Response messages traversing an interface. This count is nonzero only on upstream direction rows. This count should include the number of retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCAcks.name: docsQos3DCCAcks
docsQos3DCCAcks.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCAcks.description: The number of Dynamic Channel Change Acknowledgement messages traversing an interface. This count is nonzero only on downstream direction rows. This count should include the number of retries. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCs.name: docsQos3DCCs
docsQos3DCCs.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCs.description: The number of successful Dynamic Channel Change transactions. This count is nonzero only on downstream direction rows. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCFails.name: docsQos3DCCFails
docsQos3DCCFails.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCFails.description: The number of failed Dynamic Channel Change transactions. This count is nonzero only on downstream direction rows. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCRspDeparts.name: docsQos3DCCRspDeparts
docsQos3DCCRspDeparts.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCRspDeparts.description: This attribute contains the number of Dynamic Channel Change Response (depart) messages. It only applies to upstream direction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DCCRspArrives.name: docsQos3DCCRspArrives
docsQos3DCCRspArrives.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Downstream and/or Upstream Channel Changes section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DCCRspArrives.description: This attribute contains the number of Dynamic Channel Change Response (arrive) messages and should include retries. It only applies to the upstream direction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DbcReqs.name: docsQos3DbcReqs
docsQos3DbcReqs.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Bonding Change (DBC) section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DbcReqs.description: This attribute contains the number of Dynamic Bonding Change Requests, including retries. It only applies to the upstream direction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DbcRsps.name: docsQos3DbcRsps
docsQos3DbcRsps.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Bonding Change (DBC) section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DbcRsps.description: This attribute contains the number of Dynamic Bonding Change Responses, including retries. It only applies to the upstream direction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DbcAcks.name: docsQos3DbcAcks
docsQos3DbcAcks.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Bonding Change (DBC) section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DbcAcks.description: This attribute contains the number of Dynamic Bonding Change Acknowledgements, including retries. It only applies to the downstream direction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DbcSuccesses.name: docsQos3DbcSuccesses
docsQos3DbcSuccesses.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Bonding Change (DBC) section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DbcSuccesses.description: This attribute contains the number of fully successful Dynamic Bonding Change transactions. It only applies to the downstream direction and does not include DBC transactions that result in Partial Service. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DbcFails.name: docsQos3DbcFails
docsQos3DbcFails.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Bonding Change (DBC) section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DbcFails.description: This attribute contains the number of failed Dynamic Bonding Change transactions. It only applies to the downstream direction. Note that Partial Service is not considered a failed transaction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3DbcPartial.name: docsQos3DbcPartial
docsQos3DbcPartial.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Dynamic Bonding Change (DBC) section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3DbcPartial.description: This attribute contains the number of unsuccessful Dynamic Bonding Change transactions that result in Partial Service. IT only applies to the downstream direction. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTable.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTable
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTable.description: This object contains a log of the disconnected Service Flows in a managed device.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogIndex.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogIndex
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogIndex.description: This key indicates an unique index for a logged service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogIfIndex.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogIfIndex
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogIfIndex.description: This attribute indicates the MAC Domain Interface index where the service flow was present.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogSFID.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogSFID
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogSFID.description: This attribute indicates the identifier assigned to the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogCmMac.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogCmMac
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogCmMac.description: This attribute indicates the MAC address of the cable modem associated with the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPkts.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPkts
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPkts.description: This attribute indicates the final value of the Pkts attribute in the ServiceFlowStats object for the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogOctets.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogOctets
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogOctets.description: This attribute indicates the final value of the Pkts attribute in the ServiceFlowStats object for the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeDeleted.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeDeleted
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeDeleted.description: This attribute indicates the value of sysUpTime when the service flow was deleted.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeCreated.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeCreated
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeCreated.description: This attribute indicates the value of sysUpTime when the service flow was created.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeActive.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeActive
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogTimeActive.description: This attribute indicates the total time that the service flow was active.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogDirection.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogDirection
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogDirection.description: This attribute indicates the value of Service Flow direction for the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPrimary.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPrimary
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPrimary.description: If set to 'true', this attribute indicates that the Service Flow in the log was a Primary Service Flow, otherwise, a Secondary Service Flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogServiceClassName.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogServiceClassName
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogServiceClassName.description: This attribute indicates the value of ServiceClassName for the provisioned QOS Parameter Set of the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPolicedDropPkts.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPolicedDropPkts
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPolicedDropPkts.description: This attribute indicates the final value of PolicedDropPkts attribute of the ServiceFlowStats object for the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPolicedDelayPkts.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPolicedDelayPkts
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogPolicedDelayPkts.description: This attribute indicates the final value of PolicedDelayPkts attribute of the ServiceFlowStats object for the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowLogControl.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowLogControl
docsQos3ServiceFlowLogControl.description: This attribute when set to 'destroy' removes this instance from the object. Reading this attribute returns the value 'active'.

docsQos3ServiceClassTable.name: docsQos3ServiceClassTable
docsQos3ServiceClassTable.description: This object describes a provisioned service class on a CMTS. Each object instance defines a template for certain DOCSIS QOS Parameter Set values. When a CM creates or modifies an Admitted QOS Parameter Set for a Service Flow, it may reference a Service Class Name instead of providing explicit QOS Parameter Set values. In this case, the CMTS populates the QOS Parameter Set with the applicable corresponding values from the named Service Class. Subsequent changes to a Service Class row do not affect the QOS Parameter Set values of any service flows already admitted. A service class template applies to only a single direction, as indicated in the ServiceClassDirection attribute.

docsQos3ServiceClassName.name: docsQos3ServiceClassName
docsQos3ServiceClassName.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Service Class Name section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3ServiceClassName.description: This key indicates the Service Class Name associated with this object instance. DOCSIS specifies that the maximum size is 16 ASCII characters including a terminating zero. The terminating zero is not represented in this SnmpAdminString syntax attribute.

docsQos3ServiceClassStatus.name: docsQos3ServiceClassStatus
docsQos3ServiceClassStatus.description: The conceptual row status of this object.

docsQos3ServiceClassPriority.name: docsQos3ServiceClassPriority
docsQos3ServiceClassPriority.description: This attribute is the template for the Priority attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTrafficRate.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTrafficRate
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTrafficRate.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxTrafficRate attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTrafficBurst.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTrafficBurst
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTrafficBurst.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxTrafficBurst attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMinReservedRate.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMinReservedRate
docsQos3ServiceClassMinReservedRate.description: This attribute is the template for the MinReservedRate attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMinReservedPkt.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMinReservedPkt
docsQos3ServiceClassMinReservedPkt.description: This attribute is the template for the MinReservedPkt attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxConcatBurst.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxConcatBurst
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxConcatBurst.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxConcatBurst attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassNomPollInterval.name: docsQos3ServiceClassNomPollInterval
docsQos3ServiceClassNomPollInterval.description: This attribute is the template for the NomPollInterval attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassTolPollJitter.name: docsQos3ServiceClassTolPollJitter
docsQos3ServiceClassTolPollJitter.description: This attribute is the template for the TolPolJitter attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassUnsolicitGrantSize.name: docsQos3ServiceClassUnsolicitGrantSize
docsQos3ServiceClassUnsolicitGrantSize.description: This attribute is the template for the UnsolicitGrantSize attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassNomGrantInterval.name: docsQos3ServiceClassNomGrantInterval
docsQos3ServiceClassNomGrantInterval.description: This attribute is the template for the NomGrantInterval attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassTolGrantJitter.name: docsQos3ServiceClassTolGrantJitter
docsQos3ServiceClassTolGrantJitter.description: This attribute is the template for the TolGrantJitter attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassGrantsPerInterval.name: docsQos3ServiceClassGrantsPerInterval
docsQos3ServiceClassGrantsPerInterval.description: This attribute is the template for the GrantsPerInterval attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxLatency.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxLatency
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxLatency.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxLatency attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassActiveTimeout.name: docsQos3ServiceClassActiveTimeout
docsQos3ServiceClassActiveTimeout.description: This attribute is the template for the ActiveTimeout attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassAdmittedTimeout.name: docsQos3ServiceClassAdmittedTimeout
docsQos3ServiceClassAdmittedTimeout.description: This attribute is the template for the AddmitedTimeout attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassSchedulingType.name: docsQos3ServiceClassSchedulingType
docsQos3ServiceClassSchedulingType.description: This attribute is the template for the SchedulingType attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassRequestPolicy.name: docsQos3ServiceClassRequestPolicy
docsQos3ServiceClassRequestPolicy.description: This attribute is the template for the ReqPolicyOct attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassTosAndMask.name: docsQos3ServiceClassTosAndMask
docsQos3ServiceClassTosAndMask.description: This attribute is the template for the TosAndMask attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassTosOrMask.name: docsQos3ServiceClassTosOrMask
docsQos3ServiceClassTosOrMask.description: This attribute is the template for the TosOrMask attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassDirection.name: docsQos3ServiceClassDirection
docsQos3ServiceClassDirection.description: This attribute is the template for the Direction attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassStorageType.name: docsQos3ServiceClassStorageType
docsQos3ServiceClassStorageType.description: This attribute defines whether this row is kept in volatile storage and lost upon reboot or whether it is backed up by non-volatile or permanent storage. 'permanent' entries need not allow writable access to any instance attribute.

docsQos3ServiceClassDSCPOverwrite.name: docsQos3ServiceClassDSCPOverwrite
docsQos3ServiceClassDSCPOverwrite.description: This attribute allows the overwrite of the DSCP field per RFC 3260. If this attribute is -1, then the corresponding TosAndMask value is set to be 'FF'H and TosOrMask is set to '00'H. Otherwise, this attribute is in the range of 0..63, and the corresponding TosAndMask value is '03'H and TosOrMaskvalue is this attribute value shifted left by two bit positions.

docsQos3ServiceClassRequiredAttrMask.name: docsQos3ServiceClassRequiredAttrMask
docsQos3ServiceClassRequiredAttrMask.description: This attribute is the template for the RequiredAttrMask attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassForbiddenAttrMask.name: docsQos3ServiceClassForbiddenAttrMask
docsQos3ServiceClassForbiddenAttrMask.description: This attribute is the template for the ForbiddenAttrMask attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassAttrAggrRuleMask.description: This attribute is the template for the AttrAggregationMask attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassAppId.description: This attribute is the template for the AppId attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMultiplierContention.description: This attribute is the template for the MultiplierContentionReqWindow attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMultiplierBytesReq.description: This attribute is the template for the MultiplierBytesReq attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxReqPerSidCluster.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxReqPerSidCluster
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxReqPerSidCluster.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxReqPerSidCluster attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxOutstandingBytesP.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxOutstandingBytesPerSidCluster attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTotBytesReqPerSid.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTotBytesReqPerSidCluster
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTotBytesReqPerSid.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxTotBytesReqPerSidCluster attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTimeInSidCluster.name: docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTimeInSidCluster
docsQos3ServiceClassMaxTimeInSidCluster.description: This attribute is the template for the MaxTimeInSidCluster attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassPeakTrafficRate.name: docsQos3ServiceClassPeakTrafficRate
docsQos3ServiceClassPeakTrafficRate.description: This attribute is the template for the PeakTrafficRate attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3ServiceClassDsResequencing.name: docsQos3ServiceClassDsResequencing
docsQos3ServiceClassDsResequencing.description: This attribute is the template for the DsResequencing attribute of the QoS Parameter Set.

docsQos3PHSTable.name: docsQos3PHSTable
docsQos3PHSTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Payload Header Suppression section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3PHSTable.description: This object describes the set of payload header suppression of Service Flows.

docsQos3PHSEntry.name: docsQos3PHSEntry
docsQos3PHSEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3PHSTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the service flow of the classifier that includes this PHS rule.

docsQos3PHSField.name: docsQos3PHSField
docsQos3PHSField.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Payload Header Suppression Field (PHSF) section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3PHSField.description: This attribute indicates the Payload Header suppression field defines the bytes of the header that must be suppressed/restored by the sending/receiving device. The number of octets in this attribute should be the same as the value of PHSSize.

docsQos3PHSMask.name: docsQos3PHSMask
docsQos3PHSMask.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Payload Header Suppression Mask (PHSM) section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3PHSMask.description: This attribute defines the bit mask that is used in combination with the PHSField. It defines which bytes in the header must be suppressed/restored by the sending or receiving device. Each bit of this bit mask corresponds to a byte in the PHSField, with the least significant bit corresponding to the first byte of the PHSField. Each bit of the bit mask specifies whether the corresponding byte should be suppressed in the packet. A bit value of '1' indicates that the byte should be suppressed by the sending device and restored by the receiving device. A bit value of '0' indicates that the byte should not be suppressed by the sending device or restored by the receiving device. If the bit mask does not contain a bit for each byte in the PHSField, then the bit mask is extended with bit values of '1' to be the necessary length.

docsQos3PHSSize.name: docsQos3PHSSize
docsQos3PHSSize.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Payload Header Suppression Size (PHSS) section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3PHSSize.description: This attribute specifies the number of bytes in the header to be suppressed and restored. The value of this attribute matches the numberof bytes in the Field attribute.

docsQos3PHSVerify.name: docsQos3PHSVerify
docsQos3PHSVerify.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Payload Header Suppression Verification (PHSV) section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3PHSVerify.description: If 'true', this attribute indicates that the sender must verify that the PHS Field is the same as the content in the packet to be suppressed.

docsQos3PHSIndex.name: docsQos3PHSIndex
docsQos3PHSIndex.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Payload Header Suppression Index (PHSI) section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3PHSIndex.description: This attribute uniquely references the PHS rule for a given service flow.

docsQos3CmtsMacToSrvFlowTable.name: docsQos3CmtsMacToSrvFlowTable
docsQos3CmtsMacToSrvFlowTable.description: This object provides the mapping of unicast service flows with the cable modem the service flows belongs to.

docsQos3CmtsCmMac.name: docsQos3CmtsCmMac
docsQos3CmtsCmMac.description: This key represents the MAC address for the referenced CM.

docsQos3CmtsServiceFlowId.name: docsQos3CmtsServiceFlowId
docsQos3CmtsServiceFlowId.description: This key represents the identifier of the Service Flow.

docsQos3CmtsIfIndex.name: docsQos3CmtsIfIndex
docsQos3CmtsIfIndex.description: This attribute represents the interface index of the MAC domain of the Service Flow and where the CableModem is registered.

docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterTable.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterTable
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Service Flow SID Cluster Assignments section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterTable.description: This object defines the SID clusters associated with an upstream service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterEntry.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterEntry
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterId.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterId
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, SID Cluster ID section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterId.description: This key represents the SID Cluster ID of the SID Cluster.

docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterUcid.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterUcid
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterUcid.description: This key represents the upstream Channel ID mapped to the corresponding SID.

docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterSid.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterSid
docsQos3ServiceFlowSidClusterSid.description: This attribute represents the SID assigned to the upstream channel in this SID Cluster.

docsQos3GrpServiceFlowTable.name: docsQos3GrpServiceFlowTable
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, QoS Support for Joined IP Multicast Traffic section.
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowTable.description: This object provides extensions to the service flow information for Group Service Flows (GSFs).

docsQos3GrpServiceFlowEntry.name: docsQos3GrpServiceFlowEntry
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3GrpServiceFlowTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the group service flow.

docsQos3GrpServiceFlowIsDef.name: docsQos3GrpServiceFlowIsDef
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowIsDef.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 Operations Support System Interface Specification CM-SP-OSSIv3.0-I04-070803, Multicast Requirements Annex.
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowIsDef.description: This attribute indicates whether the GSF QOS Parameter Set corresponds to the Default Group Service Flow.

docsQos3GrpServiceFlowQosConfigId.name: docsQos3GrpServiceFlowQosConfigId
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowQosConfigId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 Operations Support System Interface Specification CM-SP-OSSIv3.0-I04-070803, Multicast Requirements Annex.
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowQosConfigId.description: This attribute indicates the Group QoS Configuration (GQC) identifier used of the creation of this GSF. The value zero indicates that the Service Flow is using the default service flow.

docsQos3GrpServiceFlowNumSess.name: docsQos3GrpServiceFlowNumSess
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowNumSess.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 Operations Support System Interface Specification CM-SP-OSSIv3.0-I04-070803, Multicast Requirements Annex.
docsQos3GrpServiceFlowNumSess.description: This attribute indicates the number of sessions that are configured in an aggregated Service Flow. If this is a single session replication, the value of this attribute is 1.

docsQos3GrpPktClassTable.name: docsQos3GrpPktClassTable
docsQos3GrpPktClassTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, QoS Support for Joined IP Multicast Traffic section.
docsQos3GrpPktClassTable.description: This object provides additional packet classification information for Group Classifier References (GCRs) in a Group Service Flow (GSF).

docsQos3GrpPktClassEntry.name: docsQos3GrpPktClassEntry
docsQos3GrpPktClassEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3GrpPktClassTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the service flow of this group classifier.

docsQos3GrpPktClassGrpConfigId.name: docsQos3GrpPktClassGrpConfigId
docsQos3GrpPktClassGrpConfigId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 Operations Support System Interface Specification CM-SP-OSSIv3.0-I04-070803, Multicast Requirements Annex.
docsQos3GrpPktClassGrpConfigId.description: This attribute indicates the GC identifier used of the creation of this GSF.

docsQos3UpChCounterExtTable.name: docsQos3UpChCounterExtTable
docsQos3UpChCounterExtTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Channel Bonding section.
docsQos3UpChCounterExtTable.description: This object provides extensions for service flow statistics for fragmentation for channel bonding.

docsQos3UpChCounterExtEntry.name: docsQos3UpChCounterExtEntry
docsQos3UpChCounterExtEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3UpChCounterExtTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the upstream Channel Interface of the service flow.

docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtValids.name: docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtValids
docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtValids.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream and Downstream Common Aspects section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtValids.description: This attribute represents the total number segments processed on this channel. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtDiscards.name: docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtDiscards
docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtDiscards.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Continuous Concatenation and Fragmentation section;[RFC 2863].
docsQos3UpChCounterExtSgmtDiscards.description: This attribute represents the total number of discarded segments on this channel due to segment HCS problems. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsTable.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsTable
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Continuous Concatenation and Fragmentation section.
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsTable.description: This object provides upstream service flow statistics for Continous Concatenation and Fragmentation (CCF). The CMTS MAY not instantate this object for service flows that do not use CCF or return the zero value on individual counter's statistics.

docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsEntry.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsEntry
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the service flow.

docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtValids.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtValids
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtValids.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Continuous Concatenation and Fragmentation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtValids.description: This attribute contains the number of segments counted on this service flow regardless of whether the fragment was correctly reassembled into valid packets. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtLost.name: docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtLost
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtLost.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Continuous Concatenation and Fragmentation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3ServiceFlowCcfStatsSgmtLost.description: This attribute counts the number of segments which the CMTS segment reassembly function determines were lost. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTable.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTable
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Data Transmission section.
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTable.description: This object defines DOCSIS MAC services primitive statistics of upstream service flows. In pre-3.0 DOCSIS devices this statistics exists per SID for either Cos or Qos services in the SNMP table docsIfCmServiceTable. A 3.0 CM with CoS configuration (DOCSIS 1.0 mode) reports the statistics defined in the SNMP table docsIfCmServiceTable. A 3.0 CM with QoS configuration reports this object regardless of whether Multiple Transmit Channel is enabled or disabled.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsEntry.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsEntry
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the service flow.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsImmed.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsImmed
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsImmed.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Bandwidth Allocation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsImmed.description: This attribute contains the number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in immediate (contention) mode. This includes only those PDUs that are presumed to have arrived at the head-end (i.e., those which were explicitly acknowledged.) It does not include retransmission attempts or mini-slots used by Requests. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsDed.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsDed
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsDed.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Data Transmission section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxSlotsDed.description: This attribute contains the number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in dedicated mode (i.e., as a result of a unicast Data Grant). Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxRetries.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxRetries
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxRetries.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Bandwidth Allocation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxRetries.description: This attribute contains the number of attempts to transmit data PDUs containing requests for acknowledgment that did not result in acknowledgment. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime for the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxExceededs.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxExceededs
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxExceededs.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Bandwidth Allocation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsTxExceededs.description: This attribute contains the number of attempts to transmit bandwidth requests which did not result in acknowledgment. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqRetries.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqRetries
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqRetries.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Bandwidth Allocation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqRetries.description: This attribute contains the number of attempts to transmit bandwidth requests which did not result in acknowledgment. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqExceededs.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqExceededs
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqExceededs.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream Bandwidth Allocation section; [RFC 2863].
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsRqExceededs.description: This attribute contains the number of requests for bandwidth which failed due to excessive retries without acknowledgment. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsSgmts.name: docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsSgmts
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsSgmts.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Upstream and Downstream Common Aspects section; RFC 2863.
docsQos3CmServiceUsStatsSgmts.description: This attribute contains the number of segments sent on this service flow. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at reinitialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated MAC Domain interface index.

docsQos3CmtsDsidTable.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidTable
docsQos3CmtsDsidTable.description: This object describes DSID information stored in the CMTS. The CMTS reports the current status of existing DSIDs. When a DSID is created during the registration process or a DBC transaction, a corresponding object instance is created. If a DSID is deleted or changed via a DBC message the corresponding object instance is deleted or updated respectively.

docsQos3CmtsDsidEntry.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidEntry
docsQos3CmtsDsidEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3CmtsDsidTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the DSID.

docsQos3CmtsDsidUsage.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidUsage
docsQos3CmtsDsidUsage.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 Operations Support System Interface Specification CM-SP-OSSIv3.0-I04-070803, Multicast Requirements Annex. DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, DSID Encodings section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
docsQos3CmtsDsidUsage.description: This attribute indicates the properties of the DSID. The bits are defined as follows: 'resequencing' This bit is set to 1 for a Resequencing DSID. 'multicastCapable' This bit is set to 1 for a DSID that is capable of transporting multicast traffic (i.e., the DSID has multicast forwarding attributes). 'multicastReplication' This bit is set to 1 for a DSID that is used for transporting a multicast replication (i.e. there is a corresponding instance of the MulticastRepl object). 'bonding' This bit is set to a 1 for a DSID that is associated with a bonding group.

docsQos3CmtsDsidDsChSet.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidDsChSet
docsQos3CmtsDsidDsChSet.description: This attribute represents the Downstream Channel Set over which the DSID is being resequenced.

docsQos3CmtsDsidReseqWaitTime.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidReseqWaitTime
docsQos3CmtsDsidReseqWaitTime.description: This attribute represents the DSID Resequencing Wait Time that is used for this DSID. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmtsDsidReseqWarnThrshld.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidReseqWarnThrshld
docsQos3CmtsDsidReseqWarnThrshld.description: This attribute represents the DSID Resequencing Warning Threshold that is used for this DSID. The value of 0 indicates that the threshold warnings are disabled. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmtsDsidStatusHldoffTimerSeqOutO.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidStatusHldoffTimerSeqOutOfRng
docsQos3CmtsDsidStatusHldoffTimerSeqOutO.description: This attribute represents the hold-off timer for reporting Out-of-Range Events via the CM-STATUS MAC Management message. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmtsDsidCurrentSeqNum.name: docsQos3CmtsDsidCurrentSeqNum
docsQos3CmtsDsidCurrentSeqNum.description: This attribute reports the value of the most recent sequence number assigned by the CMTS for this DSID. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidTable.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidTable
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidTable.description: The CMTS Debug DSID object contains the control of DSID debug statistics reporting An instance in this object defines the DSID and MAC domain to which the CmtsDebugDsidStats collects statistics for the downstream channel associated with that DSID and MAC Domain. The deletion of an instance stops the reporting of statistics for the specified DSID. This object supports instance creation and deletion. The CMTS MUST support at least one instance of this object.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidEntry.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidEntry
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the DSID.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidDsid.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidDsid
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidDsid.description: This attribute represents the DSID value to be debugged, identified by the IfIndex attribute of this object.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidRowStatus.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidRowStatus
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidRowStatus.description: The conceptual row status of this object.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsTable.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsTable
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsTable.description: The CMTS Debug DSID Stats object describes statistics at the CMTS for the forwarding of DSID-labeled downstream packets. The CMTS creates an instance for every combination of MAC Domain, DSID value, and downstream channel on which packets labeled with that DSID are transmitted. The CMTS does not delete such instances while the corresponding CmtsDebug object control instance exists.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsEntry.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsEntry
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the DSID.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsIfIndex.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsIfIndex
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsIfIndex.description: This key represents an interface index of a downstream channel that belongs to the DSID

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsidPackets.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsidPackets
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsidPackets.description: This attribute is a counter which contains the number of packets transmitted by the CMTS which are labeled with the DSID on the downstream channel. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated Downstream interface index.

docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsidOctets.name: docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsidOctets
docsQos3CmtsDebugDsidStatsDsidOctets.description: This attribute counts the number of bytes transmitted by the CMTS which are labeled with the DSID on the downstream interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime of the associated Downstream interface index.

docsQos3CmDsidTable.name: docsQos3CmDsidTable
docsQos3CmDsidTable.description: When a DSID is created, during the registration process or a DBC transaction,. The CM reports the current status of existing DSID, for example, if a DSID is deleted or changed via DBC messages the corresponding object instance is deleted or updated respectively.

docsQos3CmDsidEntry.name: docsQos3CmDsidEntry
docsQos3CmDsidEntry.description: The conceptual row of docsQos3CmDsidTable The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the DSID.

docsQos3CmDsidUsage.name: docsQos3CmDsidUsage
docsQos3CmDsidUsage.description: This attribute indicates the properties of the DSID. The bits are defined as follows: 'resequencing' : This bit is set to 1 for a Resequencing DSID. 'multicastCapable' : This bit is set to 1 for a DSID that is capable of transporting multicast traffic (e.g., the DSID has multicast forwarding attributes).

docsQos3CmDsidNumReseqChs.name: docsQos3CmDsidNumReseqChs
docsQos3CmDsidNumReseqChs.description: This attribute represents the number of channels in the downstream resequencing channel list for this DSID.

docsQos3CmDsidReseqChList.name: docsQos3CmDsidReseqChList
docsQos3CmDsidReseqChList.description: This attribute represents the Downstream Channel Set over which the DSID is being resequenced.

docsQos3CmDsidReseqWaitTime.name: docsQos3CmDsidReseqWaitTime
docsQos3CmDsidReseqWaitTime.description: This attribute represents the DSID Resequencing Wait Time that is used for this DSID. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmDsidReseqWarnThrshld.name: docsQos3CmDsidReseqWarnThrshld
docsQos3CmDsidReseqWarnThrshld.description: This attribute represents the DSID Resequencing Warning Threshold that is used for this DSID. The value of 0 indicates that the threshold warnings are disabled. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmDsidStatusHldoffTimerSeqOutOfR.name: docsQos3CmDsidStatusHldoffTimerSeqOutOfRng
docsQos3CmDsidStatusHldoffTimerSeqOutOfR.description: This attribute represents the hold-off timer for reporting Out-of-Range Events via the CM-STATUS MAC Management message. This attribute is only valid when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 1. This attribute returns a value of 0 when the Usage attribute has the resequencing bit set to 0.

docsQos3CmDsidOutOfRangeDiscards.name: docsQos3CmDsidOutOfRangeDiscards
docsQos3CmDsidOutOfRangeDiscards.description: This attribute represents the current count of out-of-range packets discarded by the CM for a given resequencing context since an in-range packet was received. docsQos3CmDsidNextExpectedSeqNum.name: docsQos3CmDsidNextExpectedSeqNum
docsQos3CmDsidNextExpectedSeqNum.description: This attribute represents the Next Expected Packet Sequence Number for a given resequencing context. docsQos3CmDsidCmInterfaceMask.name: docsQos3CmDsidCmInterfaceMask
docsQos3CmDsidCmInterfaceMask.description: This attribute represents the bitmap of the interfaces communicated to the CM in a Multicast DSID encoding.

docsQos3CmDsidFwdCmInterfaceMask.description: This attribute represents the bitmap of the interfaces to which the CM forwards multicast traffic: a logical OR of interfaces identified in CmInterfaceMask and interfaces associated with the client MAC addresses identified in the docsDevCmDsidMac instances for this DSID.

docsQos3CmDsidStatsDsid.description: This key represents the interface index of the MAC Domain associated with the DSID.

docsQos3CmDsidStatsSkewThreshExceeds.description: This attribute counts in-range sequenced packets which were successfully received by the CM after a wait time longer than the Resequencing Warning Threshold.

docsQos3CmDsidStatsOutOfRangePackets.name: docsQos3CmDsidStatsOutOfRangePackets
docsQos3CmDsidStatsOutOfRangePackets.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, Receive Channels section.
docsQos3CmDsidStatsOutOfRangePackets.description: This attribute counts the number of packets Counter received in a DSID reassembly context where the sequence number which is out of range.

docsQos3CmDsidStatsNumPackets.name: docsQos3CmDsidStatsNumPackets
docsQos3CmDsidStatsNumPackets.description: This attribute counts the total number of data packets of a DSID context forwarded for further processing.

docsQos3CmDsidClientTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-070803, DSID Encodings section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.

docsQos3CmDsidClientDsid.description: This key defines the DSID that the client MAC addresses are associated with.

docsQos3CmDsidClientClientMacAddr.description: This attribute defines a client MAC address to which Multicast traffic labeled with this DSID should be forwarded.
